Date: Fri, 12 Jun 2026 11:21:10 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 3/5] =?UTF-8?q?T-Display=20P4:=20radio=20working=20?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=E2=80=94=20HPD16A=20TCXO=20on=20DIO3=20at=201.6V?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

SX1262 init -707 root cause: calibrate-all failed because the module TCXO
(DIO3-powered, 1.6V — silently defaulted by LilyGo cpp_bus_driver) was unpowered.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 variants/esp32p4/t-display-p4/variant.h | 7 +++++--
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/variants/esp32p4/t-display-p4/variant.h b/variants/esp32p4/t-display-p4/variant.h
index 25425186d..ec20bf111 100644
--- a/variants/esp32p4/t-display-p4/variant.h
+++ b/variants/esp32p4/t-display-p4/variant.h
@@ -43,5 +43,8 @@
 #define SX126X_RESET RADIOLIB_NC
 #define SX126X_DIO1 (15 | IO_EXPANDER) // XL9535 "IO17" = register bit 15
 #define SX126X_MAX_POWER 22
-// NOTE: no SX126X_DIO2_AS_RF_SWITCH and no TCXO — matches LilyGo's own
-// radiolib_sx1262_send_receive example for this board.
+// HPD16A has a TCXO powered from DIO3 at 1.6V (cpp_bus_driver Sx126x defaults:
+// enable_dio3_tcxo=true, kOutput1600Mv). Without this, calibrate-all (0x89 0x7F)
+// fails and init returns -707. No DIO2 RF switch (SKY13453 is driven statically
+// by XL9535 IO1).
+#define SX126X_DIO3_TCXO_VOLTAGE 1.6
